		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Romania is a county in Eastern Europe bordering several countries like Ukraine to the North, Bulgaria to the South, Moldova and the Black Sea to the east. The early human settlements in Romania date back 40,000 years. During the 200 BC Romania was settled by a tribe called the Dacians. In 106 AD the Dacians were conquered and controlled by the Romans for the next 160 years. After the Romans withdrew, the area was invaded by many people including Goths, Huns and Bulgars. The Bulgar Empire that established in 681 AD was a mixture of Byzantine people as well as the Slavic tribes. In early 1300s the principality of Moldavia and principality of Wallachia emerged in this area who were then conquered by the Ottomans in 1388. After that the principalities united again to fight against the Ottomans for the next several hundred years. In 1859 the principalities officially united to form Romania.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
