				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				In 1883 fearing an invasion from Russia, Romania joined the triple-alliance of Germany Austria-Hungary and Italy and fought alongside them in World War I. During World War II Romanians along with Nazis killed many jewish people.
 
However in 1944 Romania switched sides and fought against the Nazis. After the war Soviet Union occupied Romania and used it as a satellite state under the dictatorship of Nicolae Ceausescu. In 1996 the communists regime was removed. Today Romania is a developing nation that belongs to United Nations, NATO and European Union.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
