				Geographically Romania is the largest South Eastern European country. The terrain is distributed equally between mountains and plains. The mountain ranges the Carpathians and the Transylvanian Alps create a horseshoe range. The area between the mountain ranges is called Transylvania. The Danube river that borders in the south with Bulgaria flows thru Romania into the Black Sea forming the Danube Delta.
			</p>
		</div>
		
